You are building an Expo app called GroceryApp. This is considered as the forntend of grocerybot.net.

While this integrates with api.grocerybot.net, it should be accessible offline.

Basic requirements: one must be able to:
1. Create, read, delete groceries
2. Select guilds (default is the first one from GET /guilds)
3. All data must be available offline (though no writes) - I want them to be able to use the app in the grocery store without any signals

API docs: https://github.com/verzac/grocer-discord-bot/blob/master/openapi.yaml

Integration guide: https://github.com/verzac/grocer-discord-bot/blob/master/.cursor/specs/SPEC-001-auth-rework-for-apps/integration-guide.md